.SH
2. PROFESSIONAL ACTIVITIES
.SH
2.1. Summary of activities
.PP
My research activities have been concentrated on the following four areas:
.IP "Computergraphics."
.br
Design of an interactive system for computergraphics [5, 10].
Design and implementation of ILP [8, 9, 19],
a machine-independent description language for drawings.
Development of a formal model for symmetrical input/output
functions in a graphics system [16].
Design and implementation of the control software for a
laser display/plotter (HRD-1).
.IP "Programming languages and architecture."
.br
Implementation techniques for high-level
programming languages [4, 6, 11, 14, 15, 24]
and studies on the relation between programming languages
and computer architecture [17, 18, 22].
.IP "Design of programming languages."
.br
Research in the area of programming languages for string manipulation
and pattern matching [12, 20, 27].
This has resulted in the design and implementation of the
programming languages SPRING and SUMMER.
Research on the formal definition of programming languages is reported in [23].
.IP "Programming Environments."
.br
Embedding programming languages in operating systems [21, 25].
Use of formal language definition methods as a basis for language-independent
programming environments.
Use of partial evaluation as an implementation technique for
programming environments [28].
A comparison between existing language-independent programming environments [29].
